Yakoruda
Yakoruda -LRB- -RRB- is a Bulgarian town located in the southwestern part of the country .
A part of the Blagoevgrad Province , it is the seat of the municipality which is the north-easternmost in the province .
The town lies in the Rhodope Mountains , along the Mesta River , 26 km west of the town of Velingrad .
Yakoruda was proclaimed a town on 9 September 1964 , having previously been officially classified as a village .
A plurality of the residents are Muslim Bulgarians -LRB- Pomaks -RRB- , the rest being for the most part Eastern Orthodox .
Notable natives are Survivor BG season one runner-up Ahmed Shuganov and Minister of Labour and Social Policy Emiliya Maslarova .
Municipality
Yakoruda is the seat of Yakoruda municipality -LRB- part of Blagoevgrad Province -RRB- , which includes the following 8 places :
Honour
Yakoruda Glacier on Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica is named after Yakoruda .
